Zoom appearances.
Defendant in custody at Dodge Correctional.
The State moves to delete the enhancer on count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge, deliver Fentanyl.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on 21 CF 318, to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1)	Pay court costs;
2)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3)	provide DNA sample;
4)	assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5)	maintain absolute sobriety;
6)	Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search of combination;
8)	Any other counseling, treatment, assessments as recommended by the agent;
9)	AODA assessment and follow through.
Minutes.
